 CAROLINE COUNTY, Va. -- The driver who crashed his truck on Interstate 95 south Friday morning had been shot, according to Virginia State Police. The truck crashed and overturned at the 102 mile marker in Caroline County at about 2:40 a.m.

"The driver of the vehicle was transported to VCU Medical Center via med-flight where they died from an apparent gunshot wound that was received prior to the crash," Virginia State Police spokesman Sgt. Steve Vick said. Police have closed lanes on 95 south to investigate the crash. Traffic is getting by the scene, albeit slowly.